OL,6,FThe death penalty is a legal
OL,7,Fpunishment that can be given out in 27
OL,8,Fof the US states, and 24 people died
OL,9,Fas a result of capital punishment in
OL,10,F2023, as recorded by the Death Penalty
OL,11,FInformation Centre.
OL,13,FSmiths' execution was the country's
OL,14,Ffirst attempt to use a new method
OL,15,Fsince the lethal injection was
OL,16,Fintroduced in 1982. It is now the most
OL,17,Fcommon execution method in the US.
